  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And so it was, when Israel had sown,.... Their land, and it was grown up, and near being ripe, or quite; for the Midianites gave them no disturbance in the winter, and during seedtime, when they came out of their lurking holes, and manured their land, and sowed it: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "that the Midianites came up; into the land of Canaan, from the other side Jordan, where their country lay, and which it seems lay lower than the land of Israel: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and the Amalekites, and the children of the east: the former were implacable enemies of Israel, and on every occasion would join other nations in oppressing them; and the children of the east were Arabians, as Josephus (b) expressly affirms: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "even they came up against them; all these three sorts of people in a confederacy. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(b) Antiqu. l. 5. c. 6. sect. 1.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "(b) Antiqu. l. 5. c. 6. sect. 1.",
            "children": []
