  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 3.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Children of the east",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". We first find this term in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 29:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", where it is applied to the people of Haran. Comparing the analogous phrases, \"the east country\" (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 25:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), the mountains of the east (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 23:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), \"the men of the east\" (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Job 1:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), \"the east\" (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Isaiah 2:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 2:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), we gather that the country lying to the east of Palestine as far as the river Euphrates was called the east country, and that the various tribes of Arabs and others who peopled that desert were called \"the children of the cast\" (see ver. 33 and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Judges 7:12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Judges 8:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Judges 6:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
